pageContext.claim: “Nobody's ever had rallies like this. You might have, you might have a rally like this. You might have a rally like this on the night before the election, right? The night before the election, but you'd never have rallies. These are massive everyone. Ohio was so big. Ohio. If you would have added up inside and outside you had at least 50,000 people.”
pageContext.analysis: Local media reports said "thousands" attended the rally at Pickaway County fairgrounds. There were no reports of people trying to get in, let alone 50,000 people in total, including on the outside. (Trump has previously claimed a crowd of 40,000 for this rally.)
